{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"21253d9e-8973-4c34-8fab-6b0440a647bc","content":"The directory doesn't exist yet, but I can explain what you need to configure to publish a C# MCP server as a `dotnet tool` on NuGet.org.\n\n### Required `.csproj` properties\n\nAdd these to your `MyMcpServer.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n  <PackAsTool>true</PackAsTool>\n  <ToolCommandName>my-mcp-server</ToolCommandName>\n\n  <!-- NuGet metadata -->\n  <PackageId>MyMcpServer</PackageId>\n  <Version>1.0.0</Version>\n  <Authors>YourName</Authors>\n  <Description>An MCP server for ...</Description>\n  <PackageReadmeFile>README.md</PackageReadmeFile>\n  <PackageLicenseExpression>MIT</PackageLicenseExpression>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n**Key properties:**\n- **`PackAsTool`** — makes `dotnet pack` produce a tool package\n- **`ToolCommandName`** — the CLI command users will run\n- **`OutputType` must be `Exe`** — tools must be executables\n\n### Build, pack & publish\n\n```bash\ndotnet pack -c Release\ndotnet nuget push bin/Release/MyMcpServer.1.0.0.nupkg \\\n  --api-key YOUR_NUGET_API_KEY \\\n  --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\n### Users install & run it\n\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g MyMcpServer\nmy-mcp-server          # runs via stdio\n```\n\n### MCP client config (e.g. VS Code)\n\n```json\n{\n  \"servers\": {\n    \"my-mcp-server\": {\n      \"command\": \"my-mcp-server\",\n      \"transport\": \"stdio\"\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\nWould you like me to create or update your `.csproj` file with these settings?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"010b7162-7662-4838-85d5-5bd161fd93e8","outputTokens":497,"requestId":"F3C3:BE897:1D4C2B5:219D4F5:69F54E66"},"id":"89655805-87e6-4e6d-9abc-263e477ff290","timestamp":"2026-05-02T01:07:58.735Z","parentId":"20b590be-891b-4476-ae73-15a63e771e8b"}
